# Ytils RexMd - Markdown editor for Redaxo

Zur <a href="https://rexmd.ytils.com/de/dokumentation" target="_blank"><img src="data:image/png;base64," alt="Deutsche Version" style="height: 20px;" /> **deutschen Version**</a>.

<a href="https://rexmd.ytils.com" target="_blank">Ytils RexMd</a> adds a simple but powerful Markdown editor module to your Redaxo setup.

This Redaxo Add-on is based on <a href="https://yupput.ytils.com" target="_blank">Ytils Yupput</a> by <a href="https://www.schneidersit.de" target="_blank">Kim Schneider</a> and
the <a href="https://parsedown.org/" target="_blank">Parsedown project</a> by <a href="https://erusev.com" target="_blank">Emanuil Rusev</a>.

Parts of this Add-on are based on the <a href="https://github.com/FriendsOfREDAXO/demo_addon" target="_blank">Demo-Addon</a> created by the <a href="https://friendsofredaxo.github.io/" target="_blank">Friends of REDAXO</a>.

## Using Ytils RexMd

Installing the Ytils RexMd Add-on puts a new module named ***Ytils RexMd Markdown editor*** into your Redaxo setup. 

When you switch to the editing mode, you will see a simple textarea with a button to launch the RexMd editor in the
top right corner. Press this button and watch how the magic happens. 

After RexMd opened, try to press **Ctrl+Shift+M**
to launch the dialogue (the dialogue named <a href="https://yupput.ytils.com" target="_blank">Yupput</a>) that helps you to search the 
media pool or existing articles in your Redaxo installation. 

<img src="data:image/png;base64," alt="RexMd editor launch button" style="max-width: 766px;" />

